# Maestro E2E Tests

Tests for {{name}}'s user flows.

## Structure

- `smoke.yaml` — critical path, runs on merge to main in CI (Android only)
- `full/` — full suite, runs locally on demand

## Running Locally

```bash
# Install Maestro once
curl -Ls "https://get.maestro.mobile.dev" | bash

# Run smoke tests (requires simulator/emulator/device running with app installed)
maestro test .maestro/smoke.yaml

# Run full suite
maestro test .maestro/full/

# Interactive studio (record + play)
maestro studio
```

## Writing Tests

Maestro flows are YAML. Keep them descriptive and behavior-focused:

```yaml
appId: ai.analogous.{{name}}
name: User can sign in
tags:
  - auth
---
- launchApp
- tapOn: "Sign in"
- inputText: "user@example.com"
- tapOn: "Continue"
- assertVisible: "Check your email"
```

Tag critical flows with `smoke` to include them in CI.
